        "subtopicId": "4.6",
        "title": "Electrical Energy & Power",
        "digitizedText": "## 6. Electrical Energy & Power\n\n$$\nE_e = VIt\n$$\n*\\* $t$ in seconds*\n\n$V$ - voltage  \n$I$ - current  \n$t$ - time  \n\n$$\nP = IV\n$$\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\nP &= \\frac{E}{t} \\\\\nP &= \\frac{VIt}{t} \\\\\nP &= VI\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\n### Example\n<div align=\"center\">\n  <svg class=\"sme-diagram\" width=\"250\" height=\"150\" viewBox=\"0 0 250 150\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n<!-- Wires -->\n<path d=\"M 50 40 L 50 100 L 100 100\" fill=\"none\" class=\"sme-axis\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n<path d=\"M 140 100 L 200 100 L 200 40 L 140 40\" fill=\"none\" class=\"sme-axis\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n<!-- Resistor -->\n<rect x=\"100\" y=\"90\" width=\"40\" height=\"20\" fill=\"none\" class=\"sme-axis\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n<text class=\"sme-text\" x=\"120\" y=\"105\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"12\">3 \u03a9</text>\n<!-- Ammeter -->\n<circle cx=\"50\" cy=\"70\" r=\"12\" fill=\"white\" class=\"sme-axis\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n<text class=\"sme-text\" x=\"50\" y=\"75\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"14\">A</text>\n<text class=\"sme-text\" x=\"75\" y=\"75\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"12\">5A</text>\n<!-- Battery -->\n<path d=\"M 110 30 L 110 50 M 120 20 L 120 60 M 130 30 L 130 50 M 140 20 L 140 60\" fill=\"none\" class=\"sme-axis\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n<path d=\"M 50 40 L 110 40\" fill=\"none\" class=\"sme-axis\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" />\n<text class=\"sme-text\" x=\"125\" y=\"15\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-family=\"sans-serif\" font-size=\"12\">15 V</text>\n</svg>\n</div>\n\nHow much energy is dissipated as heat by the resistor in $2\\text{ minutes}$?\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\nE_e &= 15 \\times 5 \\times 2 \\times 60 \\\\\n&= 9\\text{ kJ}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\n### Example 2\nA student connects a $6\\text{ V}$ power supply to a $3\\,\\Omega$ resistor. The resistor is left connected for $1\\text{ minute}$. How much power is dissipated by the resistor?\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\nI &= \\frac{6}{3} = 2\\text{ A} \\\\\nE_e &= 6 \\times 2 \\times 60 \\\\\nE_e &= 720\\text{ J} \\\\\nP &= \\frac{720}{60} = 12\\text{ W}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\n**Type:** Theory\n\n### Circuit Symbols\n\n| | | |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| SINGLE CELL | LAMP | ELECTRIC BELL |\n| BATTERY OF CELLS | FIXED RESISTOR | MAGNETISED COIL |\n| POWER SUPPLY | VARIABLE RESISTOR | RELAY COIL |\n| A.C. POWER SUPPLY | THERMISTOR | TRANSFORMER |\n| SWITCH | LIGHT DEPENDENT RESISTOR | AMMETER |\n| | HEATER | VOLTMETER |\n| | FUSE | GALVANOMETER |\n\n**Type:** Theory & Examples\n\n# C4: Electricity & Magnetism\n*Thursday 22/1/2026*",
