        "subtopicId": "4.8",
        "title": "Dangers of electricity",
        "digitizedText": "## 8) Dangers of electricity\n\n1) Damaged insulation\n   - exposed live wire can cause electric shock\n\n2) Overheating of cable\n   - causes insulation to melt\n   - $\\uparrow I, \\uparrow R$\n   - potential fire hazard\n\n3) Wet condition\n   - can cause electric shock if its from main power supply (AC with large current)\n\n4) Excess current flow\n   1) Faulty connection / damage insulators\n      $\\downarrow$\n      excess current will flow to earth wire\n   2) Lightning\n\n# C4: Electricity & Magnetism\n\nDate: Thursday 29/1/2026\n\n## Magnetism\n\n1) Magnetic field\n2) Electromagnet\n3) Catapult effect\n4) Electromagnetic induction\n5) Transformer\n\n---",
